Git commands:

1. Set Global User Name and Email:
git config --global user.name "Your Name"
git config --global user.email "your.email@example.com"

2. Initialize a New Repository:

git init
This command initializes a new Git repository in the current directory.

3. Clone an Existing Repository:

git clone <repository-url>
Clone an existing repository from a remote server (e.g., GitHub).
git clone https://username:token@github.com/username/repository.git

4. Add All Changes to the Staging Area:
git add .

5. Pull Changes from the Default Remote Repository:
git pull

6. Commit Changes:
git commit -m "Your commit message"

7. Push to a Specific Remote Repository:
git push origin main





